/F2 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 56.0 748.0 Tm (Draft resource pending human editorial review - not yet professionally verified.) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 56.0 730.0 Tm (An approach for prospects who already use a competitor - it respects their current) Tj
1 0 0 1 56.0 716.0 Tm (choice, asks what is and is not working, and offers a specific difference instead of) Tj
1 0 0 1 56.0 702.0 Tm (trash-talking the incumbent.) Tj
/F2 13 Tf
1 0 0 1 56.0 678.0 Tm (Learning objectives) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.0 661.0 Tm (- Respect the prospect's existing decision) Tj
1 0 0 1 66.0 647.0 Tm (- Learn what works and what they would change) Tj
1 0 0 1 66.0 633.0 Tm (- Offer one concrete, honest point of difference) Tj
1 0 0 1 66.0 619.0 Tm (- Never disparage the competitor) Tj
/F2 13 Tf
1 0 0 1 56.0 599.0 Tm (Approach in four beats) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.0 582.0 Tm (1. Acknowledge they already have a solution - no surprise, no judgment.) Tj
1 0 0 1 66.0 568.0 Tm (2. Ask what is working well before anything else.) Tj
1 0 0 1 66.0 554.0 Tm (3. Ask the one thing they would change if they could.) Tj
1 0 0 1 66.0 540.0 Tm (4. Only if there is a real gap, offer one specific difference you can stand behind.) Tj
/F2 13 Tf
1 0 0 1 56.0 520.0 Tm (Talk about them, not the competitor) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.0 503.0 Tm (- Never call the incumbent bad - it insults their choice and your credibility.) Tj
1 0 0 1 66.0 489.0 Tm (- Anchor on the change they named, not on a feature war.) Tj
1 0 0 1 66.0 475.0 Tm (- If they are genuinely happy, thank them and leave the door open.) Tj
/F2 13 Tf
1 0 0 1 56.0 455.0 Tm (Worked example) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 56.0 438.0 Tm ("You are already using Meridian - good tool, I am not here to knock it. Out of) Tj
1 0 0 1 56.0 424.0 Tm (curiosity, what is working well with it for you? ... And if you could change one thing) Tj
1 0 0 1 56.0 410.0 Tm (about it, what would it be? ... The reporting delay you mentioned is actually the one) Tj
1 0 0 1 56.0 396.0 Tm (area we are built differently, so that might be worth a look. If everything is fine) Tj
1 0 0 1 56.0 382.0 Tm (as-is, though, I will not try to talk you out of a setup that works.") Tj
/F2 13 Tf
1 0 0 1 56.0 358.0 Tm (Safe-practice note) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 56.0 341.0 Tm (Never disparage a competitor or imply the prospect made a poor choice - it damages trust) Tj
1 0 0 1 56.0 327.0 Tm (and often backfires. Only claim a difference you can genuinely deliver and demonstrate.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56.0 313.0 Tm (If the prospect is satisfied with what they have, respect that and leave without) Tj
1 0 0 1 56.0 299.0 Tm (pressure.) Tj
